// bisect: interp (Timeout: node-walk yields a div0 Value::Error, never a result) != fused (panics 'attempt to divide by zero' via wrapping_div, runtime dies) != jit (SIGFPE core-dump via unguarded x86 sdiv on zero divisor). Process exits 132 (SIGFPE).
// interp/jit: Stably reproduces across 3+ runs of both `check` (exit 132 = SIGFPE each time) and `run`. The program `i64:10 / i64:0` is a pure constant integer division — no rand/time/net/fs, no lambda/abstract-in-string, so it is fully deterministic. Three backends genuinely diverge: node-walk produces a Value::
// root_cause: Unguarded integer divide-by-zero in the fusion backends. Node-walk (canonical) at graphix-compiler/src/node/op.rs:550 `arith_op!(Div, Op::Div, false, div)` uses netidx Value's `div`, which returns Value::Error on div0. The fused-interp at graphix-compiler/src/gir_interp.rs:1984-1985 (`eval_bin`) uses `wrapping_div`/`wrapping_rem` — which still PANIC on a zero divisor (wrapping only covers MIN/-1, not div0). The JIT at graphix-compiler/src/gir_jit.rs:6267-6280 (`compile_bin`) emits raw `sdiv`/`udiv`/`srem`/`urem` with no divisor==0 guard, so x86 idiv/div traps SIGFPE. Fix: guard the divisor in 

i64:10 / i64:0
